          "start": 4,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "德，一也。一主布氣而蓄養。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 9,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "一為萬物設形像也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 16,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "一為萬物作寒暑之勢以成之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道德所為，無不盡驚動，而尊敬之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 33,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道一不命召萬物，而常自然應之如影響。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道之於萬物，非但生而已，乃復長養、成孰、覆育，全其性命。人君治國治身，亦當如是也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道生萬物，不有所取以為利也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道所施為，不恃望其報也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道長養萬物，不宰割以為利也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道之所行恩德，玄闇不可得見。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 16,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "物生而後畜，畜而後形，形而後成，何由而生？道也；何得而畜？德也；何由而形？物也；何使而成，勢也。唯因也，故能無物而不形；唯勢也，故能無物而不成。凡物之所以生，功之所以成，皆有所由，有所由焉，則莫不由乎道也。故推而極之，亦至道也。隨其所因，故各有稱焉。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道者，物之所由也。德者，物之所得也。由之乃得，故曰不得不失，尊之則害，不得不貴也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 33,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "命並作爵。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "謂成其實，各得其庇蔭，不傷其體矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "為而不有。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "有德而不知其主也，出乎幽冥，是以謂之玄德也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
